{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Sell a lifetime entitlement alongside a subscription and surface both flags through the paywall plugin."}],"sections":[],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToAddAPermanentLicense","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Overview","level":2,"text":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Many apps offer two ways to buy: a recurring pro subscription and a one-time lifetime purchase. RevenueCat models both as entitlements; "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RevenueCatPaywallService"},{"type":"text","text":" checks each independently and surfaces them as the two flags on "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"EntitlementSnapshot"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"isPro","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" — active subscription.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"hasPermanentLicense","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" — active lifetime entitlement.","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The paywall plugin’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isGateSatisfied"},{"type":"text","text":" is "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isPro || hasPermanentLicense"},{"type":"text","text":", so feature code keeps a single check while UI can branch on the underlying flags when it needs to."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For the entitlement-mapping rules and edge cases, see "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/EntitlementMapping","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"anchor":"Before-you-start","level":2,"text":"Before you start","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This guide assumes:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You have completed ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToImplementService","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You have configured ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"two","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" entitlements in the RevenueCat dashboard — typically ","type":"text"},{"code":"pro","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" for the subscription and ","type":"text"},{"code":"lifetime","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" for the one-time purchase. The identifiers are arbitrary; only the strings need to match what you pass into the service.","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"anchor":"Step-1-Pass-the-second-identifier","level":2,"text":"Step 1: Pass the second identifier","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Replace the single-entitlement init with the two-arg form:"}]},{"code":["import SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall","","let service = RevenueCatPaywallService(","    entitlementID: \"pro\",","    permanentLicenseEntitlementID: \"lifetime\"",")"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Both entitlements are now checked on every "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"customerInfo()"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"customerInfoStream()"},{"type":"text","text":" yield, and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"restorePurchases()"},{"type":"text","text":" call. The active state of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"pro"},{"type":"text","text":" flows into "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"EntitlementSnapshot.isPro"},{"type":"text","text":"; the active state of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lifetime"},{"type":"text","text":" flows into "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"hasPermanentLicense"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The two flags are independent. A user with both active gets both flags set; a user with only one active gets only that flag set."}]},{"anchor":"Step-2-Wire-the-service-into-the-plugin","level":2,"text":"Step 2: Wire the service into the plugin","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Same as the single-entitlement case — the plugin doesn’t need to know about the second identifier:"}]},{"code":["plugins.register(","    PaywallPlugin<AppState, AppAction>(","        state: \\.paywall,","        action: AppAction.paywall,","        extractAction: { if case .paywall(let a) = $0 { return a }; return nil },","        service: RevenueCatPaywallService(","            entitlementID: \"pro\",","            permanentLicenseEntitlementID: \"lifetime\"","        )","    )",")"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"anchor":"Step-3-Decide-whether-feature-code-needs-to-branch","level":2,"text":"Step 3: Decide whether feature code needs to branch","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For most gated features, keep using "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"store.paywall.isGateSatisfied"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"code":["if store.paywall.isGateSatisfied { … }"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This stays correct whether the user has a subscription or a lifetime license, and works identically in apps that don’t sell a lifetime SKU."}]},{"anchor":"Step-4-Branch-in-UI-when-copy-must-differ","level":2,"text":"Step 4: Branch in UI when copy must differ","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If the paywall sheet should be hidden for lifetime customers (so they’re not pestered to subscribe), or if the customer-center entry should be relabeled, branch on the underlying flag:"}]},{"code":["if store.paywall.hasPermanentLicense {","    Text(\"Lifetime member — thank you!\")","} else if store.paywall.isPro {","    Button(\"Manage Subscription\") {","        store.send(.paywall(.presentCustomerCenter))","    }","} else {","    Button(\"Upgrade\") {","        store.send(.paywall(.request(reason: \"upgrade-prompt\")))","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Lifetime users typically have nothing to manage in App Store \/ Settings. Hiding the customer-center button for them avoids dead-end taps."}]},{"anchor":"When-to-skip-the-second-identifier","level":2,"text":"When to skip the second identifier","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Pass "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":" (or omit the parameter) if your app has no lifetime SKU:"}]},{"code":["RevenueCatPaywallService(entitlementID: \"pro\")"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"hasPermanentLicense"},{"type":"text","text":" then stays "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"type":"text","text":" regardless of any entitlements RevenueCat reports — even if the dashboard accidentally has a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lifetime"},{"type":"text","text":" entitlement that the service is not configured to check. See the "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Lifetime entitlement is ignored when no permanent-license ID is configured"}]},{"type":"text","text":" test case for the precise behavior."}]}]}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"Related Documentation","anchor":"Related-Documentation","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/ServiceReference","doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/EntitlementMapping","doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToImplementService"]},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToImplementService","doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToPresentTheUI","doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToPreviewAndTest"],"title":"How-to Guides","generated":true,"anchor":"How-to-Guides"}],"kind":"article","variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/swiduxrevenuecatpaywall\/howtoaddapermanentlicense"]}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall"]]},"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Article","role":"article","title":"How to Add a Permanent License","modules":[{"name":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall"}]},"references":{"doc://SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/documentation/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/HowToPreviewAndTest":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToPreviewAndTest","kind":"article","role":"article","url":"\/documentation\/swiduxrevenuecatpaywall\/howtopreviewandtest","title":"How to Preview and Test","abstract":[{"text":"Drive entitlement state from SwiftUI previews and tests with ","type":"text"},{"code":"MockRevenueCatPaywallService","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" — no RevenueCat SDK call required.","type":"text"}]},"doc://SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/documentation/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/HowToImplementService":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToImplementService","kind":"article","role":"article","url":"\/documentation\/swiduxrevenuecatpaywall\/howtoimplementservice","title":"How to Implement the Service","abstract":[{"text":"Wire ","type":"text"},{"code":"RevenueCatPaywallService","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" into the ","type":"text"},{"code":"SwiduxPaywall","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" plugin so the store sees real-time entitlement updates from RevenueCat.","type":"text"}]},"doc://SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/documentation/SwiduxRevenueCa